"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-olympics-when-team-sa-is-in-action-saturday\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbOlympics: When Team SA is in action on Saturday  Team SA will have an opportunity to add to their Olympics medal haul on Saturday as the Paris Games draw towards a close.  Team SA are involved in five sports at the 2024 Paris Olympics on Saturday, witha few medal opportunities up for grabs.  There are three further track and field medals to fight for in the evening session, with Brian Raats (high jump), Jo-Ane van Dyk (javelin) and the Team SA men's 4x400m relay all in action. Van Dyk and the men's 4x400m are considered realistic medal contenders.  Team SA are currently43rd on the overall medal table, with one gold (Tatjana Smith), two silvers (Smith and men's 4x100m) and two bronzes (men's Sevens rugby and Alan Hatherly).  ATHLETICS  Men's high jump, final (7pm): Brian Raats  Women's javelin, final (7.30pm): Jo-Ane van Dyk  Men's 4x400m, final (9pm): Team SA  CANOEING  Men's kayak single 1000m semi-finals (11.20am):Hamish Lovemore  CYCLING  Men's keiren, first round heats (5.31pm):Jean Spies  GOLF  Women's individual, fourth round (12.06pm):Ashleigh Buhai is on 141 after three rounds. She's shot 68, 73 and 74 for 215.  WRESTLING  Men's 97kg freestyle, 1/8 final:Nicholas de Lange vs Givi Matcharashvili (Georgia)  Compiled by GARY LEMKE in Paris  ATHLETICS  Men's 4x400m relay, heats:Team SA finished 8th in their heat in 3:03.19 and did not qualify for the final after Antonie Nortje suffered a mishap on the third leg when he fell at the changeover. However, after the race Nigeria were disqualified and SA were promoted into the final by the referee.  Men's 800m semi-finals:Edmund du Plessis finished 4th in his semi-final in 1:45.34. This left him outside the automatic two qualifiers from the heat, and outside of being a fastest loser.  Men's 4x100m relay, final:SILVER!Team SA finished second behind Canada in an African record 37.57  CANOEING  Men's double kayak 500m semi-finals:Hamish Lovemore and Andrew Birkett finished 6th in 1:29.70. The top 4 boats went through, so the Team SA duo qualified for the B-final  Men's double kayak 500m B-final:Lovemore and Birkett finished 4th in 1:31.79. That means they ended their campaign in 12th position  DIVING  Women's 3m springboard final:Julia Vincent finished 11th in the final, with a total score of 271.25 points. She had risen to as high as third after three of the five dives.  IN PROGRESS  GOLF  Women's individual, third round  -8Lydia Ko (NZ)  -7Zhang Rose (USA), Morgane Metraux (Swit)  -6Mariaju Uribe (Col), Miyu Yamashita (Japan), Atthaya Thitikul (Thai)  Team SA golfers  -1 (T16th)Ashleigh Buhai (68, 73, 74, 215)  +11(T49th)Paula Reto (78, 73, 76, 227)  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"